Shortest Job First (SJF) is a CPU scheduling algorithm where the process with the smallest burst time executes first.
It is usually non-preemptive in basic OS practical programs.

Steps of SJF
Enter number of processes.
Enter burst time for each process.
Sort processes based on burst time (ascending).
Calculate Waiting Time (WT).
Calculate Turnaround Time (TAT).

Formulas:
Waiting Time (WT) = Sum of burst times of previous processes
Turnaround Time (TAT) = Burst Time + Waiting Time
